{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567590","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567590"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:04:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:04:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19161"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19161"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.21,0.57,0.04,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11895"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86191"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11895"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19161"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70460"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5354"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"12736"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27858"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27909"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28046"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86191","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/86191"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes racism that occurs through established policies and practices within healthcare organisations?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Internalised racism","Systemic racism","Institutional racism","Interpersonal racism","Cultural racism"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInstitutional racism\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the policies, practices, and procedures within organisations that, whether intentionally or not, produce outcomes that chronically disadvantage certain racial groups. In healthcare, this can manifest through inflexible appointment systems, location of services, or culturally inappropriate care delivery models.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInterpersonal racism\u003C/strong\u003E describes direct discriminatory interactions between individuals, such as racial prejudice from healthcare workers towards patients\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternalised racism\u003C/strong\u003E occurs when people accept negative messages about their own abilities and intrinsic worth based on their racial or cultural identity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECultural racism\u003C/strong\u003E involves the cultural assumptions that position one culture\u0027s values and beliefs as superior to others\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESystemic racism\u003C/strong\u003E is broader than institutional racism, encompassing how racism operates across multiple interconnected systems in society\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these different forms of racism is crucial for healthcare workers to identify and address barriers to equitable healthcare access and outcomes for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Institutional racism refers to discriminatory policies, practices, and cultural representations within organisations and institutions that disadvantage certain racial groups.","Systemic racism describes how racism is embedded throughout interconnected societal systems, creating widespread disadvantage.","Interpersonal racism involves direct discriminatory actions or prejudices between individuals."],"references":["Australian Health Ministers\u2019 Advisory Council. Cultural respect framework 2016\u20132026 for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Health. Canberra: AHMAC; 2016. Available from: https://www.health.gov.au/resources/publications/cultural-respect-framework-for-aboriginal-and-torres-strait-islander-health-2016-2026","Paradies Y, Truong M, Priest N. A systematic review of the extent and measurement of healthcare provider racism. J Gen Intern Med. 2014;29(2):364-87. Available from: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11606-013-2583-1","Ben et al. Racism Data in Australia: A Review of Quantitative Studies and Directions for Future Research. Journal of Intercultural Studies. 2024. https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/07256868.2023.2254725#abstract","Royal Australian College of General Practitioners (RACGP). The National Guide to a preventive health assessment for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. 3rd ed. East Melbourne, Vic: RACGP; 2018. Available from: https://www.racgp.org.au/download/Documents/AHU/National-Guide-3rd-Ed-Sept-2018.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70460"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19161"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70460","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70460"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-19T19:25:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-19T19:26:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11895"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86191"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGr